    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Candles used for the Christian feast of the Epiphany on January 6, which celebrates the recognition of Jesus by the three Magi. These candles are used in homes and liturgies. Example of design include a candle terminating in three upper branches (shaped like a trident) and a large candle encircled by three crowns.</Note_Text>
